<HR><H2>[COLD] Mail Filtering</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Tue Jul 22 18:13:54 1997
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Tue, 22 Jul 1997 16:02:52 -0600 (MDT)
From: Brandon Gillespie &lt;brandon@roguetrader.com&gt;
To: coldstuff@cold.org

To allow for better mail filters, the cold mail lists should now be sent
from 'Cold-Owner.LIST@...', so procmail or whatever you use for filtering
can simply watch for anything from 'Cold-Owner.*@' and it should be from a
cold list (the hostname its from may change, as I beat my sendmail
configuration into submission with virtual hosts--for now it'll be
roguetrader).

-Brandon Gillespie

</PRE>
